< user_name>
Kenny B< /user_name>
<date>1512315059044< /date>< Text>
The staff are friendly and bilingual--English and Spanish. I would occasionally see the owner (no clue if they were the actual owners or not, but I'd see them fix up the place and work on the machines from time to time when I was small).

I have been coming here since I was in middle school, and they've come a long way in upgrading: there is now a "lounge" where you can sit on orange stools and use your laptop or phone in the back (WiFi is free,  countertops have an outlet above them that supports USBs to charge your phone if you need it), and a support desk in the middle as you walk in.

They offer five different sizes of washers, and a laundry service. Dryers and folding tables are located on both sides, and although some  dryers have better heat, they're responsive to feedback, and will get whatever problem solved if it's within their reach.

The two coin machines are located on the right from the entrance, along with vending machines for laundry supplies and/or snacks.

The restroom is NOT public: you must pay 25c.

Folding tables and machines are constantly wiped down by the staff. Floors also are swept/mopped. There is a sink before the support desk.

Only problem is that parking is sometimes an issue because of the surrounding shops or heavy traffic in the laundromat, but I usually park towards the middle of the lot anyway, if anything.

Personally, I always come back because of the cleanliness + WiFi!<//Text>

<Text>The prices are good, especially for this area of downtown, but you get what you pay for. The salads are basic compared to the other offerings in the WaterCourt but aren't bad and it is good to have a reasonable choice for food. Extremely limited indoor seating (2 four-tops, 1 six-top, 9 bar seats) and during the lunch hour, the employees on break take up half the seating and then leave their trash for someone (presumably another employee?) to clean up. Plenty of outdoor seating when the weather is nice. Strangely, no trash cans inside. You need to walk outside to throw away your trash...I guess that is why the employees leave their trash in the seating areas.</Text></record>

< Review>
I had a telehealth visit with the Doctor a few months back. I was telling him what I was looking for. I was mainly looking for things I could do or consume that could possibly help me fight my hair loss. He helped me so much by sending me a list of things that I could do to try and same my hair and also some things that could be causing my hair loss.

I found out I was consuming a couple things that could be causing hair loss. So I immediately stopped using them. I also started using the products which he suggested for hair growth. Now it's too soon to really know how this is going to turn out, but I am hoping for the best.

< Review>
This is my second FUE procedure.  I didn‚Äôt do my first FUE with Dr Behnam.
There are several differences between the two experiences.
Dr. Behnam does the entire procedure himself.  He discusses with me where to prioritize to have hair transplanted to maximize the fullness look since I have limit amount of donors.  He draws on my scalp and shows me pictures of it.  My first procedure was done by two technicians.
After the surgery Dr. Behnam gives me a spray and an Acell cream to reduce the chance of scab formation and to cut down the healing time for the donor area.  It might help regrow some of the donors back.  I wish I had that in my first operation.
Dr. Behnam texts me that night and he even wakes up before 6 am to reply my text.  It is impressive.
I drive from San Diego to do my surgery with Dr Behnam.  It so worths the driving and the traffic.  Thank you Dr Behnam<//Review>

Who would‚Äôve thought I‚Äôd be getting a hair transplant and how did I end up with Dr Sean with the hundreds of other options in LA?

I started noticing him through his replies on forums just from basic google searches. Does it hurt, realistic goals, cost involved, fue vs fut, etc.

Then I read a few articles about him and decided to go in for a consult.

I didn‚Äôt meet with his partner/hype man Steve(I think that‚Äôs his name... sorry if it‚Äôs not Steve) I met with Dr Sean. We talked about options, expectations and the procedure.

Of course the hair line I wanted wasn‚Äôt what he was going to be able to accomplish on the first try... but he‚Äôs really honest from the beginning. ‚ÄúIf you want thickness and a natural look for your age this is what I‚Äôm going to do.‚Äù I liked that and I knew he was the guy. (Once you meet him you‚Äôll know too)

$500 deposit later and I was scheduled for my day about 2 months later (he performs 1 per day and is pretty booked).

I went with the cheaper fut, he thought the fue method was not necessary for me. I will probably do the fue next time as healing is wayyyy easier.

Okay day of surgery. It‚Äôs an early start and the team is there and ready. They made it as accommodating and comfortable as they could for me. It‚Äôs painless except for the local he gives you where the cut is made on the back of your head. To me that was painful. Like it hurt. (But maybe I‚Äôm soft lol but once that starts working it‚Äôs painless the rest of the day)

I drove home that day. I was tired and stressed but I drove 15 miles home.

Post:
He gives you his cell phone! He wants you to text him and call him. And well I did.

I had a few issues in the post procedure. Nothing to do with his procedure or instructions though I will say is the first day or two when you have to keep the area wet with a solution he gives you he wants you to irrigate it with some pressure not just keep it wet. That‚Äôs where I went wrong.

The cut in the back of the head is a little painful after and the healing process in general is gross and stressful but that‚Äôs just the procedure wherever you go. Don‚Äôt expect to look kind of presentable for atleast a month or two.

Regardless I made it though. Almost a year later and I‚Äôm a new man. Is it like Brad Pitt‚Äôs hair? Not exactly but it‚Äôs damn close!

Him and his team are great and I highly suggest you go with them on your hair transplant as it‚Äôs an art form too and Dr Sean created the paint brush.</Review>

<Text>I was in a car accident in 2009 that left me with a laceration to the scalp, for which I needed medical attention  The resulting scar was about 2 inches across and about half an inch wide.  For 8 years I either had to comb my hair a certain way to hide the scar or had to wear a hat.  I visited Dr. Sean Behnam after reading positive reviews online about people who received hair transplants for balding and wondering if he could do something about my noticeable scar.  Dr. Sean told me that he could treat the scar with a FUE hair transplant procedure that would make the scar invisible.  I communicated to him my fear that the individual transplanted hairs would die in the scar tissue, but he reassured me that they would successfully graft and grow in the scar tissue because of the placental lining solution he uses in the FUE procedure.  I was told to take it easy for about three weeks after surgery, and I did do the follow-up care as Dr. Sean instructed.  The hair started growing out of the scar about three months later and the hair strands eventually become thicker, which surprised me.  The scar is gone.  I can now comb my hair normally and don't have to wear a hat when I cut my hair short.  Dr. Sean transformed my life.  I'm no longer conscientious about the scar like I use to be!  I highly recommend seeing Dr. Sean to treat scalp scars!</Text><pictures>None< /pictures>< Resp>

< review>
Just had an FUE procedure done with Dr. Sean. It‚Äôs only been a week, so my review is based on the experience.
I live in the Bay Area but chose Dr. Sean after taking into account multiple factors: 1) member of IAHRS 2) Great reviews on Yelp and Google 3) Amazing Youtube video explaining in great details everything you need to know pre-op, op and post-op. 4) consultation was great. He went over everything: cost, what to expect, what not to expect and other details. 5) Amazing personality. Warm, friendly and professional. You can tell he absolutely loves what he‚Äôs doing and takes great pride in his work
I saw 3 others doctors in NorCal&SoCal + Bosley + virtual consultation from Turkey and finally selected Dr. Sean.
He personally called me the night of procedure, which was very kind of him
On the day of procedure, he evaluated whether FUT or FUE is better for me. We agreed to do FUE. He initially told me he will only do my front and probably no crown this time.
He had a hookah-style laughing gas to get me ready for the numbing. I have very low pain tolerance but I was okay with it. I laid on my stomach for 2 hours while Dr extracted the grafts. I had 1 bathroom break. I would recommend not drinking coffee the morning of operation. The less bathroom breaks you take and the less you move, the more grafts he can extract (don‚Äôt make him lose his momentum). He had 4 nurses who were taking the grafts from doctor and separating them into 1,2 and 3 hair follicles. He told me he was happy to actually extract ~2900 grafts for me!! Which was amazing news. Of course prior to operation I gave him the thumbs up that he can extract as much as possible.
We took a lunch break where I ate and watched his staff work on my grafts. After lunch, they started the insertion. Again, the hookah nitrogen gas and numbing. He made the incisions himself on the front and my crown which I was super happy about.  Once that part was done, two of his staff started inserting the grafts while he monitored them. The staff took turns so not to get tired. Remember, 2900 grafts means: 2900 drilling + 2900 extraction + 2900 incisions + 2900 planting!! So it‚Äôs A LOT of work. The doctor did the ~9000 first three parts himself and the staff did the last part. His staff were amazing!! We watched a movie and were talking about all sorts of things! It was fun.
The second part is tedious. You‚Äôre sitting for a good 4 hours or more. Your legs get super tired but thanks to the hookah laughing gas, you get through it somehow.
Overall, the procedure took almost 11 hours (including morning consultation and prep + lunch and operation and post operation). It‚Äôs a long day. I‚Äôm glad I‚Äôm stayed at the hotel next door to his office so I just walked back to hotel in like 30 seconds.
I saw the doctor next day and also on the day on my flight. He cleaned up my area, cleaned my hat for the airport and went over everything again.

I‚Äôve been back for 2 days now. I send him pictures every morning for him to see and so far so good.

Overall, I was super happy with the experience. Amazing doctor, amazing staff. Let‚Äôs hope for amazing results soon (let‚Äôs hope for somewhere in between Elvis and George Constanta)

Will definitely update this review with results.

Thanks again Dr. Sean and your amazing staff.</review>

< Review>
Dr. Sean Behnam is the BEST of the BEST!

I did a ton of research before selecting Dr. Sean and I actually traveled from Hawaii to his office in California.  His office made it so easy, there is a nice hotel next door, and they arranged all of the accommodations.  All I had to do was check-in the night before the procedure date, and everything else was prepared and ready for me.

- FUE Procedure Day -

I arrived early in the morning and they started right away.  Dr. Sean only does one procedure per day, so 100% of the staff attention was on me, and I felt so comfortable the entire time.  The staff was very professional and they were so nice throughout the entire procedure.

There was almost no pain at all!  Dr. Sean has a special technique, that he developed himself, to numb his patients.  It not only makes it easier, but there are no needles!!!  Throughout the entire procedure Dr. Sean explained what was going on and was always available if I had any additional questions.

About half-way through the procedure Dr. Sean's staff brought me a delicious lunch, and they also provided great snacks throughout the day.  They really went above and beyond to make me comfortable!

Before I knew it, I was done!  It went quicker than I thought and I was ready to go back to my hotel room and relax.  They gave me a great post operation kit that had all of the supplies needed to properly clean and protect the procedure.

Dr. Sean called me often to make sure things were still looking good, and if I had any questions I could text him directly!  He always would take the time to answer my questions. < Review>
Back in 2012 my doctor recommended Dr. Behnam when I asked about a hair restoration specialist. That alone says a lot because anyone my doctor recommends is usually excellent in both medical skills and people skills. I still shopped around for a bit but had the hair graft procedure done shortly after with Dr. Behnam. Very quickly I knew I would write them a glowing review, but also knew from doing research beforehand (shopping around) that most of the reviews were from people who'd recently gotten the procedure done, so I thought I'd wait a bit.
So finally after 2 years I decided it's about time I write this review, because after all this time I'm still just as impressed with my experience there. They are extremely people-friendly, it feels more like visiting family than going to a clinic (his twin brother's dermatologist practice is in the same office so it does have a family practice feel.) He's the only doctor I've ever known that actually gives his cell phone number after surgery, so if you have any issues / questions you can contact him immediately. That's amazing- I don't think any other doctor does that.
Even though my doctor recommended Dr. Behnam I still shopped around and quickly found that Dr.  Behnam's practice had the best rates around- I figured probably in part because they have a nice office on the second floor instead of a 7th floor penthouse like some practices, but it's also obvious that Dr. Behnam is not in it for the money- and ultimately that's what makes the biggest difference here. Contrary to so many places, he only does one procedure per day. So you get his full attention and all his effort and energy on doing the best possible job for you instead of rushing through you to get to the next guy on the list. Every other place I looked into did at least 2 patients per day. (one morning, one afternoon)
As for the procedure itself, I was very satisfied with the results and the operation itself. They made me feel comfortable the day of, and after just a few months waiting for the grafts to grow, for the first time in years I could comb my hair backwards instead of hiding my bald spot.
Included in the price are visits for the laser chair thing, which helps stimulate hair growth. So after all those visits I really came to see that these guys are the real deal. Just good people passionate about what they do, no bullshit, and doing a really good job. If you are not a good candidate for the procedure, he will tell you. That kind of honesty is hard to find in an industry that is known for greedily exploiting people's insecurities.
So yeah, in conclusion I highly recommend Dr. Behnam!<//Review>

The next step is to wait for the hair to grow out slowly, looking forward to the effect.
Dr. Sean is highly recommended here!

(Translated by Google) Impeccable work and service that I highly recommend!

From the first free consultation, during which he does an objective analysis and projection while taking your expectations into account, until the day of the procedure, Dr. Sean takes great care to prepare you in the best possible way and in the best possible conditions.
A team of 4 people is 100% dedicated to you during (often) the 2 days that the operation lasted.

The hair transplantation procedure was performed by the FUE method. A method almost under pain and without sequelae (procedure performed over a year ago). He will be able to explain the different methods that exist very well.

Professional support before and after the operation to obtain the best possible results.

This procedure was something I dreaded because there is no room for error. Dr. Sean was able to give me confidence by clearly explaining the steps and means used to make the operation a success.

I couldn't have gotten better service anywhere in Los Angeles. I have met several specialists in hair transplants but, Dr. Sean really stood out, I do not regret choosing him and highly recommend him to anyone wishing to have a hair transplant.

<name>Lenny Rabin</name><user>108700214800573447897</user><Response>None</Response>< Gmap_id>
0x80c2964d54783115:0x6d5fb32336573ae5< /Gmap_id>
<date>1551676379797< /date>< review>
I heard they had the best falafel on the west coast and my god they were amazing. Crispy on the outside and perfect wet texture on the inside. They were super flavorful and so savory.

The Moroccan cigars you can tell are home made and made with love. These are not frozen from restaurant depot. Each is hand rolled and stuffed with meaty goodness.

Hummus was fresh and perfectly spiced. The pita were also warm, fluffy and toasted to perfection.

If you are down for some Cholent or Jachnun - both Shabbat delicacies. Then come on Sunday and these items are LIT.

Their grilled chicken plate was super flavorful and just so fresh and light. I can eat that all day.

The ambiance is fresh, airy and most importantly CLEAN. I met the owners, a very sweet and welcoming Israeli woman and her Moroccan husband. You get the feeling they transported their home countries to the Valley and all of the hospitality, flavors, and dishes are made with that purpose.

Would go again!

P.S. the pickled veggie bar, the home made olives, the nana tea, the Turkish coffee, the baklava bites, the cabbage salad... all spot on.</review>
</record></dataset><record>

< review>
I have ordered from Palermo's Pizza twice. The first time it took an hour and 15 mins for me to receive my delivery which was cold when it arrived. I live about two miles from the restaurant. I called the restaurant and they adjusted my bill. I appreciated the customer service and ordered from them again a few weeks later. This time the delivery arrived within an hour. I ordered the pizza pasta combo. The pizza was cold. The pasta (fettuccini) came with meat sauce, which was not listed on the menu and seemed odd. It tasted ok. That night I had such a bad stomach ache that I had trouble sleeping. For the next five days that followed that meal I had food poisoning. I called the restaurant to complain and the manager said nonchalantly  "oh yeah, a lot of people got sick."  So if you want cold food or E. coli then this is the spot for you.</review>

< Text>
I popped in unexpectedly, after I had a hybrid system failure while driving on the freeway. I contacted Stockton Hyundai and they said to tow it right there.

It has been about 3 years since I have been there, as I get oil changed elsewhere. However, I walked in and Xavier immediately recognized me and even remembered my name. This guy is a class act. Although my car is now past warranty, he still fought to get it covered. Hyundai wasn't having it, but I truly appreciate the effort.

I was given a promise date and price. Not only did they get it done a day early, it came in slightly under the estimate. My only gripe, is that the mechanic forgot to completely closed the hood. Had it not been for a really windy day, I would not have noticed it. It could have been worse, but it was caught before anything happened.

Aside from that I love Stockton Hyundai and I love my car. After 110,000 miles, this is the first time I have had a problem...and it didn't break the bank. That's reliability that will keep me around for a long time.< /Text>

I've been shopping around for a Sonata for a few months now but haven't pulled the trigger. When I came around Stockton Hyundai who was having a great deal on a 2015 Sonata Hybrid I figured now was the time. I went down on Saturday and worked some numbers, wasn't satisfied with the deal so I walked.... After re-working the numbers all night I decided to call the dealership back the next morning and tell them the deal I wanted and laid out the numbers. I was told I would get a call back and waited around. Still no call back by Monday, so I called Monday morning and was told I would be called back. When it finally reached the afternoon I decided the only way I would get answers was to physically be in the store. I went to the store and ended up re-working the deal that I worked on Monday. UGH! It felt like no one knew the numbers I had discussed on Saturday. I ended up being able to negotiate a bit more since this was now my second trip to the dealership and I was determined to leave with the car. I ended up walking with the deal that I wanted, but felt that better communication between the dealership staff could have led to a better car buying process. As I'm a loyal Hyundai lover! I would return here to purchase again, but hope that a communication process is in process the next time around.</Text>

What kind of car is equipped with a 12 volt battery with a 3 year life span, and why is it $285!?! I haven't picked it up yet but I'm hoping someone takes care of this to keep customers happy. I paid $32,000 for this car 4 years ago. We've had constant rattling of the sunroof which has been worked on twice. It's back in for that again. Sunroof leaks but they said they don't see the problem so I guess we have to deal with a leaky roof in the rain on a car that's still pretty new. Now the dash is blinking DO NOT DRIVE, CHECK CHARGING SYSTEM. But since they don't cover the battery that is supposedly causing the problem, I was given the offer to pick it up and drive off like that. By the way, I am not the only hybrid Sonata owner that has this issue. I searched online for this problem and there are others as well as YouTube videos of it. Should there not have been a recall? If they take care of that battery I'll change my review. The service guy at the counter is great but he can't do everything. I blame the service technicians and the Hyundai corporation for lack of customer care. I was next considering buying an SUV from them because I love my car but after this I'm not sure. I'll do this in parts. Bare with me you wanna know this. I'm not a difficult person or like to complain but I gotta warn people. Haha

I went online to shop around for Hyundai elantra and this dealership had very competitive prices, almost too good to be true. I was looking at one vehicle specifically and I made a appointment to see that vehicle. I drove over two hours to get there and when I get there they tell me that competitively priced vehicle sold the previous day (it's a lie) and they baited and switched me to another similar vehicle that was more money and in worse condition. On top of that the second vehicle they showed me, that vehicles listing online had false information. They listed that vehicle with pictures of another vehicle without seat staining to trick people into thinking that the vehicle is in good condition. I had to point out to them that the pictures they had up for that vehicle online isn't the same car due to features that were missing due to it being a lower trim model, they acted surprised but they know what they're doing.

Every single vehicle I got into and looked at was filthy and not a single car I saw didn't have stains set in the seats. There were cars with 2k miles with stains everywhere! Dog hair, crumbs.. it was weird.

I test drove another vehicle, we got back, sales guy (Salvador) disappeared and the finance guy fast tracked me to the desk and started asking my numbers. Credit score, down payment, trade in, etc. I told him that we haven't even negotiated the price of the vehicle yet so I'm not ready to give numbers. HE TOLD ME THE VEHICLE PRICE WASN'T NEGOTIABLE. They didn't care, seems like they didn't want the sale.

If he would have worked with me I would have bought a car that day. Credit was above 800 but I had cash to buy the car outright.. we never got there. I'm going to Honda instead.

P.S. To my initial sales guy Salvador you're a great sales guy, you should have stuck with me instead of handing me off to some finance guy that didn't even know the car I was trying to buy.</Review>

111430564304002323919<//UserId.>
<Pics>None<//Pics><date>1516907329623</date><gmap_id>0x80900cc8669b8a83:0x5ca1220efc19bdba</gmap_id><Name>Kristein Osuna</Name>< Review>
On Monday January 22, 2018 my phone rang at 4:36 am , it was my daughter Rickie , "Mommy I need you and Mario , I was just Tboned on my way to work on the driver side and the guy took off, I need you now"  I had to get to my daughter as fast as I could 15 minutes away , not knowing if she was hurt, pinned in the car , or ok. I picked up mario from work because he dropped his phone on his way out the door that morning.
Within 10 minutes I made it to my daughter. I pulled up saw she was out of the car unhurt, thank you to my daddy for always keeping us safe. She was checked out and was found with a bump on her head. Her 1993 Toyota Tercel was a total loss. That little car was good to he and kept her safe.
After a few hours she called me again , " Mommy ( no mater what age they all call me Mommy) can you come get me and take me to get a car, life continues, I would like to see if I can get the Elantra . So I took her to Stockton Hyundai. We pulled up, she knew what she wanted and could afford. Chris came out and we spoke for a minute , he went and got the car she wanted. We went on a Test Drive , not just around the block but on the freeway for a few miles. Yes Rickie was still shaken from the accident but she did great. We got back and not having the best credit she was unsure she would be able to get the car she had fallen in love with. Chris asked us to let him do his job. I could not cosign , she had to do it on her own.
Monday turned out to be the Lucky day for my daughter, she was unhurt from the accident  and Chris and the amazing finance manager worked magic and Rickie was signing papers for a 2018 Hyundai Elentra SE . This car was her first big girl purchase , she is 29 and works hard has two beautiful step-daughters , a wonderful boyfriend, and needed a safer, bigger car for her family.
I cannot stop crying happy tears each time I think of the way the whole staff at Stockton Hyundai made this happen for my daughter. I will never stop telling people how they helped her.
They say on the website , good credit or bad credit we will help you . And they speak the truth.
Thank you again Chris for All you have done !</Review>
